
- Change Variable name throughout the class: 
  Select--> Alt + Shift + R ---> Rename
  
- Run Java Program : Ctrl + Optional(Function Key) + F11  
  
- Search a Java File : Ctrl + Shift + R 
- Change Tabs : Ctrl + PageUP  or Ctrl + PageDown 
- Jump Forward /Backward : Alt + Left Arrow  or Alt + Right Arrow
   
- View Call Hierarchy : Ctrl + Alt + H
- View Class Hierarchy : Select the class --> F4


- Go to a Line ---> Ctrl + L ---> Enter Line Number
- Jump to Beginning/End of () {} [] ---> Ctrl + Shift  + P

- All UpperCase: Ctrl + Shift + X
- All LowerCase: Ctrl + Shift + Y

- Delete Entire Row : Ctrl + D

- Move Code Up : Alt + Up
- Move Code Down: Alt + Down
 (Up/Down can be done for mulitiple lines also, just select those lines then Alt +Up/Down)
 
 - Surround Code with Various stuff : Alt + Shift + Z
   For Eg. add try/catch , add if/else, add Loop etc 
   
- Shortcut for Creating Getters/Setters or Constructors :
  Right Click in that class anywhere --> Go to Source
  
- Format code : Ctrl + A -->  Ctrl + Shift + F  

- Optimize(Add/Remove) Imports : Ctrl + Shift + O

- Comment / Un-Comment
  Single Line : Select that line : Ctrl + /
  Multi Line Comment : Select --> Ctrl + Shift + /
  
- Increase/Decrease the Font Size ---> Ctrl + "+" or Ctrl + "-"

- To Complete the Write Code Automatically : Ctrl + Space 
  For Eg. type (Syso,main,for,while,if,...etc) and 
  then hit Ctrl + Space--> Select and Enter to auto complete
  
- Create/Extract Method : Alt + Shift + M
- Jump to Method/Variable Implementation --> F3 or Ctrl + Click
- OutLine of the Class - Ctrl + O   

- To See All the ShortCuts : Ctrl + Shift + L
~Source: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LIGkIGdmHII&list=LL&index=22